hpnicfDot11QoS.name: hpnicfDot11QoS

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfDot11QoS.description: This MIB provides information about WLAN QoS configuration. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. WMM WMM is a wireless QoS protocol designed to preferentially transmit packets with high priority, thus guaranteeing better QoS services for voice and video applications in a wireless network. EDCA Enhanced distributed channel access (EDCA) is a channel contention mechanism designed by WMM to preferentially transmit packets with high priority and allocate more bandwidth to such packets. AC Access category (AC), is used for channel contention. WMM defines four access categories; they are AC-VO (voice), AC-VI (video), AC-BE (best-effort), and AC-BK (background) in the descending order of priority. When contending for a channel, a high-priority AC preempts a low-priority AC. CAC Connection admission control (CAC) limits the number of clients that are using high-priority ACs (AC-VO and AC-VI) to guarantee sufficient bandwidth for existing high-priority traffic. U-APSD Unscheduled automatic power-save delivery (U-APSD) is a new power saving mechanism defined by WMM to enhance the power saving capability of clients. SVP SpectraLink voice priority (SVP) is a voice priority protocol designed by the Spectralink company to guarantee QoS for voice traffic.

HpnicfDot11WMMSVPMapAC.name: HpnicfDot11WMMSVPMapAC
HpnicfDot11WMMSVPMapAC.description: The AC level which SVP packets are assigned to. acbk : for background access category, acbe : for best-effort access category, acvi : for voice access category, acvo : for video access category, disable : for disable SVP feature

HpnicfDot11WMMCACPolicy.name: HpnicfDot11WMMCACPolicy
HpnicfDot11WMMCACPolicy.description: The policy of CAC. channelUtilization : the channel utilization-based admission policy for CAC, userNumber : the users-based admission policy for CAC

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmCfgTable.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmCfgTable
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmCfgTable.description: The table defines the basic parameters for WMM configuration.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmCfgEntry.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmCfgEntry
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the basic information for WMM configuration.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEnabled.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEnabled
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEnabled.description: Represents the status of WMM in radio. 'true' : The WMM function is enabled. 'false': The WMM function is disabled.

hpnicfDot11RadioSVPMapToAC.name: hpnicfDot11RadioSVPMapToAC
hpnicfDot11RadioSVPMapToAC.description: Represents the AC level which SVP packets are assigned to. 'acbk' : Specifies the AC-BK (background traffic) queue. 'acbe' : Specifies the AC-BE (best-effort traffic) queue. 'acvi' : Specifies the AC-VI (video traffic) queue. 'acvo' : Specifies the AC-VO (voice traffic) queue. 'disable' : Disable SVP packet mapping.

hpnicfDot11RadioCacPolicy.name: hpnicfDot11RadioCacPolicy
hpnicfDot11RadioCacPolicy.description: Represents the policy for CAC. CAC requires that a client obtain permission of the AP before it can use a high-priority AC for transmission, thus guaranteeing bandwidth to the clients that have gained access. CAC controls real time traffic (AC-VO and AC-VI traffic) but not common data traffic (AC-BE and AC-BK traffic).

hpnicfDot11RadioCacChlUtlValue.name: hpnicfDot11RadioCacChlUtlValue
hpnicfDot11RadioCacChlUtlValue.description: Represents Maximum channel utilization rate, that is, the medium time of the accepted AC-VO traffic and AC-VI traffic to the valid time during the unit time. This object can be set only if the value of hpnicfDot11RadioCacPolicy is ChannelUtilization.

hpnicfDot11RadioCacUserNum.name: hpnicfDot11RadioCacUserNum
hpnicfDot11RadioCacUserNum.description: Represents the users-based admission policy for CAC. This object can be set only if the value of hpnicfDot11RadioCacPolicy is userNumber.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgTable.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgTable
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgTable.description: The table defines the basic parameters for EDCA configuration of radio.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgEntry.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgEntry
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the basic information for EDCA configuration of radio.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmAC.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmAC
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmAC.description: Represents the AC level index of EDCA parameters of radio. 'acbk' : Specifies AC-BK (background traffic). 'acbe' : Specifies AC-BE (best-effort traffic). 'acvi' : Specifies AC-VI (video traffic). 'acvo' : Specifies AC-VO (voice traffic).

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmAifsn.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmAifsn
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmAifsn.description: Represents AIFSN parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEcwMin.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEcwMin
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEcwMin.description: Represents ECWmin parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be smaller than ECWmax parameter.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEcwMax.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEcwMax
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEcwMax.description: Represents ECWmax parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be larger than ECWmax parameter.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmTxoplimit.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmTxoplimit
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmTxoplimit.description: Represents TXOPLimit parameter of EDCA, the value must be in the range of 0 to 65535 (in units of 32 microseconds). The TXOP value of 0 indicates that only one MPDU can be transmitted. The range of this argument is limited by the radio chip capability.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmNoAck.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmNoAck
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmNoAck.description: Represents the AC to adopt the No ACK policy. The protocol defines two ACK policies: Normal ACK and No ACK.

hpnicfDot11StationWmmEdcaTable.name: hpnicfDot11StationWmmEdcaTable
hpnicfDot11StationWmmEdcaTable.description: The table defines the basic parameters for EDCA configuration of station.

hpnicfDot11StationWmmEdcaEntry.name: hpnicfDot11StationWmmEdcaEntry
hpnicfDot11StationWmmEdcaEntry.description: This entry contains the basic information for EDCA configuration of client. If CAC is enabled for an AC, CAC is also enabled for ACs with higher priority. For example, if CAC is enabled for AC-VI, CAC is also enabled for AC-VO. However, enabling CAC for AC-VO does not enable CAC for AC-VI.

hpnicfDot11StationWmmAC.name: hpnicfDot11StationWmmAC
hpnicfDot11StationWmmAC.description: Represents the AC level index of EDCA parameters of client. 'acbk' : Specifies AC-BK (background traffic). 'acbe' : Specifies AC-BE (best-effort traffic). 'acvi' : Specifies AC-VI (video traffic). 'acvo' : Specifies AC-VO (voice traffic).

hpnicfDot11StationWmmTxoplimit.name: hpnicfDot11StationWmmTxoplimit
hpnicfDot11StationWmmTxoplimit.description: Represents TXOPLimit parameter of EDCA, the value is in units of 32 microseconds. The TXOP value of 0 indicates that only one MPDU can be transmitted.

hpnicfDot11StationWmmCacEnabled.name: hpnicfDot11StationWmmCacEnabled
hpnicfDot11StationWmmCacEnabled.description: Represents the AC to adopt the No ACK policy. The protocol defines two ACK policies: Normal ACK and No ACK. Only if the value of hpnicfDot11StationWmmAC is 'acvo' or 'acvi', Cac can be set correctly here.

hpnicfDot11WmmResetRadioByAP.name: hpnicfDot11WmmResetRadioByAP
hpnicfDot11WmmResetRadioByAP.description: Clear the WMM statistics information of the radio of the specified AP or all radios. The meaning of this object is the same as hpnicfDot11APElementIndex, it represents the index of AP element. If the value of this object is set to 0xFFFFFFFF, WMM statistics information of all radios will be cleared. The value of this object is always 0 with the get operation.

hpnicfDot11WmmResetStationByAP.name: hpnicfDot11WmmResetStationByAP
hpnicfDot11WmmResetStationByAP.description: Clear the WMM statistics information of the clients associated with the specified AP, or of all clients. The meaning of this object is the same as hpnicfDot11APElementIndex, it represents the index of AP element. If set with the 0xFFFFFFFF, it will clear the WMM statistics information of all clients. The value of this object is always 0 with the get operation.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Table.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Table
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Table.description: The table defines the basic parameters for EDCA configuration of radio.

hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Entry.name: hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Entry
hpnicfDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Entry.description: This entry contains the basic information for EDCA configuration of radio.

hpnicfDot11RdWmmAC.name: hpnicfDot11RdWmmAC
hpnicfDot11RdWmmAC.description: Represents the AC level index of EDCA parameters of radio. 'acbk' : Specifies AC-BK (background traffic). 'acbe' : Specifies AC-BE (best-effort traffic). 'acvi' : Specifies AC-VI (video traffic). 'acvo' : Specifies AC-VO (voice traffic).

hpnicfDot11RdWmmAifsn.name: hpnicfDot11RdWmmAifsn
hpnicfDot11RdWmmAifsn.description: Represents AIFSN parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability.

hpnicfDot11RdWmmEcwMin.name: hpnicfDot11RdWmmEcwMin
hpnicfDot11RdWmmEcwMin.description: Represents ECWmin parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be smaller than ECWmax parameter.

hpnicfDot11RdWmmEcwMax.name: hpnicfDot11RdWmmEcwMax
hpnicfDot11RdWmmEcwMax.description: Represents ECWmax parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be larger than ECWmax parameter.

hpnicfDot11RdWmmTxoplimit.name: hpnicfDot11RdWmmTxoplimit
hpnicfDot11RdWmmTxoplimit.description: Represents TXOPLimit parameter of EDCA, the value must be in the range of 0 to 65535 (in units of 32 microseconds). The TXOP value of 0 indicates that only one MPDU can be transmitted. The range of this argument is limited by the radio chip capability.
